16/04/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- A French helicopter carrying six French tourists crashed Sunday (April 15th) in Sekersu Plateau near Turkey's Black Sea coast. 
Nuri Okutan, governor of the nearby province of Trabzon, said all the passengers and crew were safe. 
The group was headed for the picturesque Kaskar Mountains.
In other news Sunday, state-run Anadolu agency reported that another Turkish soldier was killed during a clash with guerrillas from the terrorist Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) in the predominantly Kurdish province of Tunceli. 
Security forces reportedly killed six PKK members. 
(Zaman, Turkish Daily News - 16/04/07; Reuters, AP, Xinhua - 17/04/07)
